Guys, just watched a video called "SCP: Dollhouse"
Def recommend it.  Short little tactical horror film.
Honestly, the SCP universe is PERFECT for the horror genre
It answers the question: "What if you had special ops trained for very specific threats, but even that training is never enough?"
Typical problem with any sort of military horror film
The threat is either so easily counterable that you wonder how it got so out of hand
Or it's so god damn effective you wonder how they even put up a defense? xD
So one suffers from extreme incompetence, the other major plot armor
SCP finds that nice balance where you can overcome it, but the risk of casualties is super high~

I spent the first 2.5 hours of my shift just cleaning
Nothing but cleaning (maybe a lil register duty). But mostly cleaning
Our one competitor is down for the next 2 weeks while they're disinfected, so our store is getting more traffic
And what do I walk into?  Apparently no fucking CLEANING
The entire coffee bar was a fucking disaster area.  Coffee grounds everywhere

Dried coffee stains.  Dried creamer puddles, caked on sugar.  A giant fucking coffee spill that got everywhere.  The drip catchers for the creamers looked like they hadn't been cleaned since the last day I was there
Most of that 2.5 hours was spent cleaning up that disgrace.  I am now putting all immediate family on notice, DON'T SHOP WHERE I WORK
I don't trust that my coworkers are actually sanitizing the store properly, if at all, and I personally wouldn't buy a damn thing from there anymore until this whole thing is over.
So the question becomes, if I wouldn't buy something from where I work, then why, in the name of all that is good an holy, would I still want to work there?
On top of that, I'm just WAITING for a write up, or a "talk" with my manager because nothings getting "done" on my shift
Do you regret asking, Ord? xD
You had a bit to get off your chest
That level of stress is no good
sucks, leaving a job now.  But you can't do everything and get punished for it
I can guarantee my parents will just tell me some variation of "suck it up"
But I am seriously waiting for some kind of reprimand
For the past few weeks, there have been multiple items on the checksheet that I haven't been finishing because there's so much to do
